spanGrp.span: Ha should not be there according to Griet.
they are staying at the veepos ...
bly in die pos met die skape
Griet: no na in the repeatition, could be analyzed as: /hnga ǀʼhoa pos/
and the man drive out the sheep, they go away
a ǂoo ǃxain ǁhuu ǀoaxu, a hng ǁʼae,
toe jaag die manne skaap uit, lat hulle loop / toe loop hy met die skaape veld toe
hng is not actually heard, but Griet repeats it
(he) goes with them and looks after (them)
ǁʼae nǀa hngke, ǁʼaa ng ǃʼui,
gaan hy met hulle, en loop pas hulle op / hy saam met hulle geloop
ask Griet/ ask again - lUna is of little help, says something about saam loop
and goes and looks after them
hng is badly heard and this is lUna's interpretations that it is there
die vrou is by die huis ...
add glossing for a with ? mark
Griet does not repeat a on the first word, lUna is ok with a
the woman sits inside the house
a ǀaeki ǀʼii soo nǁang ǁaʼen,
die vrou sit in die huis
sy sit en doen die naaldwerk ...
sy sit en doen die naaldwerk
the child is playing, the child is playing
ǀaba kaǃkxʼora ng ki ǀaba kaǃkxʼora,
die kind speel, die kind speel
a is sometimes there in the repetition and sometimes not, lUna repeats it with a, e, ke or he.
the beginning is badly heard, Griet repeated it as kinn, but it is more like hng, lUna heard it as either hng or he for a REL.SG.
Not clear whether ke is really there.
she carries the child on the back
and they (the woman and her child) ...
toe hulle (die vrou en die kind) ...

(the bull) comes, attacks (the house), digs (the ground)
the woman went to her husband
vrou is na die man toe
(the woman) goes and tells her husband
(die vrou) geloop, sy sê vir die man
Griet says she stutters at the beginning, lUna interorets it as ku
they (the woman and her husband) look after the sheep
hulle pas, pas die skaap op
kom dra hulle die gras OR hulle loop steek nou die gras
the beginning sounds like /kinn ke ǃoon/
not clear what ǃoo really is, lUna repeats it as ǃoon or ǃan
They want to burn to burn the grass to frighten the bull.
they (the woman and her husband) come
toe loop sê hulle vir die Boere
(man) "the bull is standing, it is fighting ...
it (the bull) is still standing there and fighting
ki noxoba nǃaaʼa ki a ǁʼaan,
hy staan en baklei nog daar
what is this e , maybe a
the Boer says to them: "hey, sleep here now
ǀʼhuun ku ng kike, "hey, ʘunn nou ki a",
check again lUna has no idea what the ng ke ka portion is, changed after discussion of Martina to ng kike
nǁng is hardly heard, but Griet insists on having pronounced it. kxʼunu - maybe OBLIG, ask lUna
on the next day they again ...
they (the Boer and the man) arrive
hulle (die boer en die man) kom
die boer kom en hy sien
it (bull) is still standing, it is fighting
he (the Boer) says to that man:
"jy moet maar nou my skaap toe gaan
jy kom bly nou hier op die plaas"
the woman is at the farm
die vrou is op die plaas
hy staar soo, hy is daar
what is the second word, lUna has no idea
then they (the Boer and the man) take the bull, they ...
toe laai hulle die bul op ...
they come, they slaughter it (the bull)
hulle kom, hulle slag hom op en hulle laai hom op die motor car
